        <svcsubproc>
            <title>2585355C91 KIT, AUXILIARY (SNOWPLOW) LIGHT Instructions</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">This instruction sheet covers installation of Auxiliary light wiring, switch and
                    programming.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Dash Harness (3588838C91)</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect Battery Power.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect System Controller Connector (4007 Brown). Insert terminals from service
                    harness (3588838C91) as shown below:
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f7300073" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg73/G73000AH.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Remove and tape or shrink-wrap any already existing terminals. Reconnect Connector.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover from power distribution center (PDC). Insert into mini fuse block M-2
                    (4002) the following relay terminals:
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f7300074" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg73/G73000AI.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Insert (2) relays (3519350C1) into fuse block and lock with 3536085C1(2) and 3555642C1.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert terminals into the Dash to Forward Chassis Harness connector on the dash side
                    (4301) as shown below:
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f7300075" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg73/G73000AJ.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Remove and tape or shrink-wrap any already existing terminals.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert circuit 64HI into auxiliary connector (4305M) part number 2039311C91 in cavity
                    "A" as shown:
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f7300076" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg73/G73000AK.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Plug remaining cavities with plug (587579C1) and insert lock (2039342C1).</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tie - Wrap service harness as necessary</para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <title>Forward Chassis Harness (3560224C92)</title>
            </para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Insert terminals into the Forward Chassis to Dash harness connector on the forward chassis
                        harness side as shown below: Remove and tape or shrink-wrap any already existing terminals.
                        Route harness along existing harness and tie wrap as needed. Note on some 4000 series models,
                        service harness may need to be routed on engine side of washer bottle, to allow enough length
                        for horn and radiator ground to connect. Re-connect Dash to forward chassis connectors.
                        <emph type="bold">NOTE: If this connector exists on service harness, remove terminals, lock,
                            seal and discard connector, lock and seal.
                        </emph>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Connect Dash 7-Way connector (2039312C91) to Forward chassis 7-Way connector (2039311C91).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Connect horn connector, radiator ground to service harness connectors, taping away existing
                        connectors.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Connect left and right headlight/turn signal connectors using service harness connectors,
                        taping away existing connectors.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Tie - Wrap service harness as necessary.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <figure id="f7300077" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg73/G73000AL.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <title>Programming and Switch</title>
            </para>
            <para>Reprogram ESC using ICAP or the Diamond Logic&#8482; Builder software (See authorized International
                Dealer). If vehicle is equipped with fog lights (595019), this feature must be removed prior to adding
                Snow Plow lights (595099). ICAP or the Diamond Logic&#8482; Builder software will determine the location
                of the plow light switch.
            </para>
